table_description.rank: Rank - This is a count of the rows from top to bottom. It is recalculated following the sorting of a column.
table_description.nation: Nationality of the player. First, we check our records in international play at senior level. Then youth level. Then citizenship presented on wikipedia. Finally, we use their birthplace when available.
table_description.position: Position most commonly played by the player. Examples: GK - Goalkeepers, DF - Defenders, MF - Midfielders, FW - Forwards, FB - Fullbacks, LB - Left Backs, RB - Right Backs, CB - Center Backs, DM - Defensive Midfielders, CM - Central Midfielders, LM - Left Midfielders, RM - Right Midfielders, WM - Wide Midfielders, LW - Left Wingers, RW - Right Wingers, AM - Attacking Midfielders.
table_description.competition: Competition. Number next to competition states which level in the country's league pyramid this league occupies.
table_description.age: Age at season start. Given on August 1 for winter leagues and February 1 for summer leagues.
table_description.tackles_won: Tackles Won - Tackles in which the tackler's team won possession of the ball.
table_description.blocks: Number of times blocking the ball by standing in its path.
table_description.tackles_plus_interceptions: Tackles plus Interceptions - simple sum of tackles and interceptions.
table_description.errors: Errors - Mistakes leading to an opponent's shot.

table_description.passes_completed: Passes Completed - Includes live ball passes (including crosses) as well as corner kicks, throw-ins, free kicks and goal kicks.
table_description.passes_attempted: Passes Attempted - Includes live ball passes (including crosses) as well as corner kicks, throw-ins, free kicks and goal kicks.
table_description.key_passes: Key Passes - Passes that directly lead to a shot (assisted shots).
table_description.passes_into_final_third: Passes into Final Third - Completed passes that enter the attacking 1/3 of the pitch (not including set pieces).
table_description.passes_into_penalty_area: Passes into Penalty Area - Completed passes into the 18-yard box (not including set pieces).
table_description.crosses_into_penalty_area: Crosses into Penalty Area - Completed crosses into the 18-yard box (not including set pieces).
table_description.progressive_passes: Progressive Passes - Completed passes that move the ball towards the opponent's goal line at least 10 yards from its furthest point in the last six passes, or any completed pass into the penalty area. Excludes passes from the defending 40% of the pitch.
